column2: TINDAKMALAYSIA NETWORK SERVICES PLT (TINDAK MALAYSIA)

Election Commission of Malaysia (SPR), Tindak Malaysia (2024), Attorney General Chambers, Straits Times (https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/pn-and-ph-candidates-to-face-off-in-sungai-bakap-state-by-election-in-penang),Media Ulamak Official (YouTube), Elections Lab

This is the non-gazetted official result from SPR. All police voters entitled to be early voters opted to be postal voters; hence, no early voting activity was required. Only 51 saluran level data out of 67 are shown due to incompleteness of data display during SPR FB Live. Some of the Saluran level results for candidate votes and total valid votes were computed by Tindak Malaysia.  TindakMalaysia Network Services PLT is not responsible for any errors or omissions arising from the original data or its derivatives
